newJobID

public java.lang.String newJobID(java.lang.String existingJobId)
Generates a JobID based on an existing JobID. The new JobID is the existing one suffixed with the string [Alces yyyy-MM-dd HH.mm.ss.SSS]. If the new JobID is longer than 63 characters (a limitation required for conformance with CIP4's Base ICS) the existing JobID is trimmed so that the length of the new JobID is exactly 63 characters.

Specified by:
newJobID in interface JobIDFactory
Parameters:
existingJobId - a string used as a prefix for the new JobID generated
Returns:
a new JobID of maximum length 63 characters
